naive /naɪˈiːv/

CET6 TEM4 

1. ADJ If you describe someone as naive , you think they lack experience and so expect things to be easy or people to be honest or kind. 幼稚的 

例： It's naive to think that teachers are always tolerant. 认为老师总是很宽容是幼稚的。 

例： Their view was that he had been politically naive. 他们的看法是，他在政治上曾是幼稚的。 

2. naively ADV 幼稚地 

例： ...naively applying Western solutions to Eastern problems. …幼稚地用西方的办法来解决东方的问题。

